headline: This 12 Dividend Stock Portfolio Will Pay Your Bills – Every Week
summary: Most dividend stocks pay quarterly—but your bills don’t. Rent, groceries, gas, surprise car repairs… life doesn’t come once every three months. That’s why some investors are building what’s called a Weekly Paycheck Portfolio—a curated list of dividend-paying stocks staggered to deliver consistent income every week of the year. headline: Luxury Development Edition Birmingham Secures £127.5 Million Backing From Eldridge
summary: LONDON, July 21, 2025--Court Collaboration and Select Property, the strategic partners behind Edition Birmingham, one of the city’s most prestigious residential developments, have today announced a £127.5 million loan from Eldridge Real Estate Credit, the real estate investing strategy of Eldridge Capital Management.

headline: 3 Reasons PRU is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the last six months, Prudential’s shares have sunk to $103.65, producing a disappointing 13.8% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 4.1% gain. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
